This VFS plugins provides access to the Linux based IP stack and can be used
with together with our libc or VFS server.

The plugin is loaded and configured within the <vfs> node:

!
! <vfs>
!   <dir name="dev">
!     <jitterentropy name="random"/>
!   </dir>
!   <dir name="socket>
!     <lxip random_path="/dev/random" dhcp="yes"/>
!  </dir>
! </vfs>

Configuration attributes:

:'dhcp': Bool, use DHCP to obtain IP address, gateway, and nameserver

: 'ip_addr'
  'netmask'
  'gateway'
  'nameserver': IPv4 addresses can be used for static address configuration

: 'mtu': Number, set the maximum transfer unit (default 1500)

: 'random_path': This is mandatory and should point to a target that generates
                 random data (vfs_jitterentropy in the example above.
